<TITLE> EC seeks troops deployment from Dec 12 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 12 (bdnews24.com)  The Election Commission on Wednesday asked the government to keep law and order maintenance troops deployed during December 12-31 to ensure security through the general and upazila polls. "The probable timeframe for deployment of the armed forces has been considered to begin December 12 and terminate at least three days after the upazila elections," EC secretary M Humayun Kabir told reporters. He spoke to the media the after a coordination meeting with the various stakeholders involved in the national polls. The EC secretary also mentioned that troops were usually deployed four days ahead of similar events. Through their deployment period, the law-enforcement troops will keep out of the polling centres and act as reserve and striking forces, Kabir said. "The number of required troops will be determined later and publicised through home ministry circulars." The EC secretary said they had asked the finance ministry for election budgets. The budget for law and order maintenance will be tailored as soon as the number of the troops to be posted is determined, he added. The preparatory meeting was held to ensure coordination among the actors of the polls affairs, Kabir said. Chief election commissioner ATM Shamsul Huda, the two election commissioners Sohul Hosain and Sakhawat Hossain, director general of BDR major general Shakil Ahmed, Armed Forces Division director brigadier general Kazi Abdus Samad, home joint secretary Maksumul Hakim Chowdhury, inspector general of police Noor Mohammad, Ansar and VDP director general ATM Amin, M Shams Khan of National Security Intelligence, Sheikh Mamun Khaled of Directorate General of Forces Intelligence, Coast Guard director general commodore Maksumul Kader, RAB director general HM Khandakar and Additional IGP Baharul Alam attended the coordination meeting. bdnews2
